  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best free web hosting provider?",
  "response": "When looking for the best free web hosting provider, it's important to consider factors such as storage space, bandwidth, ease of use, and additional features like website building tools or support for specific content management systems. Here are some of the top free web hosting providers:\n\n1. **InfinityFree**:\n   - **Storage**: 5GB\n   - **Bandwidth**: Unlimited\n   - **Key Features**: Free website builder, supports custom domains, cPanel access, and a variety of scripts like WordPress.\n   - **Pros**: High storage and unlimited bandwidth, user-friendly.\n   - **Cons**: Ads on free accounts, slower performance compared to paid hosts.\n\n2. **ByetHost**:\n   - **Storage**: 1GB\n   - **Bandwidth**: 50GB\n   - **Key Features**: cPanel access, supports PHP and MySQL, free website builder.\n   - **Pros**: Reliable for small sites, good for beginners.\n   - **Cons**: Limited storage and bandwidth, ads on free accounts.\n\n3. **000webhost**:\n   - **Storage**: 1GB\n   - **Bandwidth**: 10GB\n   - **Key Features**: Supports WordPress, website builder, cPanel access.\n   - **Pros**: Easy to use, good for small personal sites.\n   - **Cons**: Limited resources, ads on free accounts.\n\n4. **GitHub Pages**:\n   - **Storage**: 1GB per repository\n   - **Bandwidth**: Unlimited\n   - **Key Features**: Static site hosting, integrates with GitHub repositories, supports custom domains.\n   - **Pros**: Free for open-source projects, no ads, good for developers.\n   - **Cons**: Only for static sites, no database support.\n\n5. **Google Sites**:\n   - **Storage**: 15GB (shared with Google Drive)\n   - **Bandwidth**: Unlimited\n   - **Key Features**: Easy drag-and-drop builder, integrates with other Google services.\n   - **Pros**: Simple to use, no ads, good for basic websites.\n   - **Cons**: Limited customization, no support for advanced web applications.\n\nEach of these options has its strengths and limitations. If you're looking for a balance of storage, bandwidth, and ease of use, **InfinityFree** might be the best choice. However, if you're a developer focused on static sites, **GitHub Pages** could be more suitable. Always consider your specific needs and the potential limitations of free services when making your decision.",
